R1: Chores are seen to be appropriate things for a robot to do, especially since cleaning robots (i.e. iRobot/Roomba) already exist. They often perform their tasks around people, children, pets, etc. Robots are precise, they can handle carrying various objects without problem. The only thing that might be seen as slightly inappropriate is starting conversations with people - robots are seen as passive conversation partners, not active.
R2: This seems to be a social gathering so cleaning or moving furniture would be seen as inappropriate.
R3: The direction is away from people so cleaning/carrying things is fine, but not starting a conversation.
R4: Carrying small objects/food while passing people is fine, so is starting conversation with them. Cleaning/carrying large objects isn't.
R5: Carrying food or large objects in the direction that directly crosses the path of another person could be dangerous.
R6: Carrying objects/cleaning while walking into another person/inside a group is inappropriate, but starting a conversation amidst them is fine.
R7: The robot is far enough away from all the people in the room and the dog, and the circle is small.
R8: Vacuuming while others are talking is seen as rude, most of the people are on the other side of the room so it's fine to tidy up/carry small things.

R10: the robot would bump into the person in its path and talk to them with its back turned to the others
R11: the robot is moving away from the group so it can mop/carry things but not start a conversation or vacuum (it'd drown out their conversation)
R12: if the robot is "serving" the people in the conversation
R13: robot is in the middle of a group of people
R14: robot would have to be very careful about not colliding with the person closest to it
R15: robot is an appropriate distance away from everyone else in the room
R16: robot would have to be very careful about not colliding with the people closest to it, especially since there is music playing
R17: robot would have to be very careful around the person on the edge of its circle

R1: The robot doesn't have anyone in front of him... and so, any social interaction (like starting a conversation) is inappropriate. However, he can make some chores around the house by himself.
R2: The robot is now facing a wall. He can be vacuuming and mopping that floor... but any social interaction or object carrying seems inappropriate.
R3: In that direction, the robot can make a lot of chores. However, in the dining room there is a group socializing... and so the robot must avoid any activity that can disturb the conversation... like vacuuming (noise), transport big objects...
R4: The group seems to be talking...the robot could bring some food/drinks to the group... but once again he should avoid any noisy activities.
R5: He is too close to one person... he can be offering food, drinks or he could actually talk. However, any other house chore is inappropriate.
R6: Once again he is very close to a person... We could serve any drinks or food. However, any other house chore is inappropriate .
R7: The table is near. The robot could be cleaning the area and picking up some drinks or cold food left by the group.
R8: It is a pretty small area but i think that the robot could be doing home chores that do not involve noise.
R9: The robot is really close to the group... we could be distributing food/drinks... however some people do not like this type of proximity. Additionally, he is giving is back to the rest of the group... it's quite disrespectful.
R10: He should not be cleaning, vacuuming or mopping and running over that person. Once again it seems to close to distribute food/drinks or start conversations.
R11: He left the group. He could be bringing food or drinks left from them, but since the group is socializing, any other house chores should be avoided.
R12: Once again he could be talking or serving the person in front of him...but he is giving is back to the rest of the group... some people could find it inappropriate.
R13: The same situation. He could be serving the person, but he is giving his back to the rest of the group.
R14: there are some people around him... We could be picking /mopping... but once again he should avoid noisy activities... he should not disturb the group.
R15: The group is dispersed...he could actually be cleaning the space (and taking leftovers). He can use the vacuum since there is no personal interaction.
R16: The music is playing...probably someone is trying to listen. In that case, vacuuming should be avoided. The rest of the house chores are appropriate.
R17: Once again, the majority of the house chores can be made.. if someone is actually trying to listen to the music, vacuuming should be avoided.
R18: House chores can be made. The robot doesn't have anyone by his side, so it's inappropriate to start a conversation. The room has some people... it could be dangerous carrying big objects,.
R19: The robot should be aware of that person right by his side. He should not carry big objects, drinks, food, vacuuming, cleaning or mopping.
R20: He seems to be to close too that group. He could be serving them some drinks and food. Any other house chores are inappropriate.

R1: It's inappropriate for a robot to be doing anything that could endanger the health of a child who could move unexpectedly (e.g. spilling a hot food over their head)
R2: In this situation, it would be inappropriate for the robot to make the environment dangerous (bottom of the stairs wet and slippery by mopping or blocking the staircase) while there are people attempting to climb the stairs.
R3: In this setting, the robot is far enough removed from people to do the majority of housework; however he's not facing any of the humans, therefore starting a conversation would not be appropriate.
R4: The robot is moving directly into a group of people who appear to have a conversation; therefore interrupting them with housework would be inappropriate.
R5: It would be really inappropriate to mop the floor or vacuum clean straight through a group of people.
R6: The robot appears to be directly engaged by the humans, possibly serving them; to carry out chores in this situation would be highly inappropriate.
R7: The robot doesn't appear to be interacting with anyone in the scene, doing its work quietly in the background, so none of the abovementioned actions would be inappropriate.
R8: The activity circle of the robot intersects with a zone where a human is resting, any noisy activity would be inappropriate.
R9: The robot is likely serving the humans (food, drinks) or being istructed by them, any chores would interrupt their conversation.
R10: The direction would take the robot ramming directly into a human, only reasonable course of action for the robot is advising the human to watch out in case a change of direction is no longer possible.
R11: Moving away from a group of people, the robot definitely shouldn't be trying to start a conversation.
R12: Inside a close group of people, it's very inappropriate to do the chores.
R13: Anything in this situation would be inappropriate except for asking the human to let the robot pass.
R14: The path of the robot is at risk of intersecting a path of a human, it could be dangerous to carry hot food.
R15: Whenever there is a child in the room, the robot should be extra careful with anything that can spill or harm a child.
R16: It would be inappropriate to drown the music with the noise of a vacuum cleaner.
R17: It would be inappropriate to drown out the usic with the noise of the vacuum cleaner.
R18: There is no arrow in the picture provided.
R19: It would be inappropriate to perform noisy or dangerous activities directly behind a person's back.
R20: It's inappropriate to do chores within such a close range of humans.
